{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17526695","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17526695"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T15:24:43+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T15:24:43+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14148"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14148","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14148"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.78,0.16,0.02,0.02,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6831"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55839"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6831","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6831"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14148"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41385"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"707"},{"type":"tags","id":"1315"},{"type":"tags","id":"1571"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4954"},{"type":"tags","id":"4980"},{"type":"tags","id":"4983"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4989"},{"type":"tags","id":"4990"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5686"},{"type":"tags","id":"11634"},{"type":"tags","id":"11638"},{"type":"tags","id":"11643"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"15431"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44845"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55839","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/55839"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 15-year-old girl presents to the General Practice clinic with her parent. She requests a prescription for oral contraceptives. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. During a confidential discussion with the girl alone, she demonstrates a clear understanding of the risks and benefits of oral contraceptives and expresses a strong desire to start taking them. Her parent, however, is strongly opposed to the idea of contraception for religious reasons.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate course of action?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Prescribe contraceptives without informing the parent","Insist on family counselling before making a decision","Refuse to prescribe contraceptives due to parental objection","Report the situation to child protective services","Refer the patient to a gynaecologist"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis scenario presents an ethical dilemma involving the concept of mature minor consent and parental rights. The most appropriate course of action is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eprescribe contraceptives without informing the parent\u003C/strong\u003E, assuming the healthcare provider has assessed the patient to be a mature minor capable of making this decision.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERefusing to prescribe contraceptives due to parental objection\u003C/strong\u003E fails to respect the autonomy of the mature minor. In many jurisdictions, the concept of Gillick competence allows minors to consent to medical treatment if they demonstrate sufficient understanding and intelligence to comprehend the nature and implications of the proposed treatment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInsisting on family counselling before making a decision\u003C/strong\u003E may be helpful in some situations, but it\u0027s not necessary if the minor is deemed competent to make the decision independently. Moreover, it could potentially violate the patient\u0027s confidentiality and autonomy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReferring the patient to a gynaecologist\u003C/strong\u003E is unnecessary in this case. General practitioners are typically capable of prescribing oral contraceptives, and there\u0027s no indication of a need for specialist care.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReporting the situation to child protective services\u003C/strong\u003E would be inappropriate. Seeking contraception is not a sign of abuse or neglect, and such a report would violate the patient\u0027s privacy and trust.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis scenario highlights the importance of assessing a minor\u0027s capacity to consent to medical treatment, respecting patient autonomy, and maintaining confidentiality. While parental involvement is often beneficial in pediatric care, there are situations where a mature minor\u0027s right to make medical decisions may override parental preferences, particularly in matters related to reproductive health.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Mature minors may have the capacity to make their own medical decisions, even if their parents disagree.","The concept of Gillick competence allows for assessment of a minor\u0027s capacity to consent to medical treatment.","Healthcare providers must balance respect for patient autonomy with the duty to protect vulnerable individuals."],"references":["Bird S. Consent to medical treatment: the mature minor. Medicus. 2011 Oct 1;51(9):54-55. Available at: https://www.racgp.org.au/getattachment/85c539df-7518-45fc-af6f-c760dd04f8ba/Consent-to-medical-treatment-the-mature-minor.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41385"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14148"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"41385","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/41385"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-10-18T11:59:44+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-18T11:59:44+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6831"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"55839"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"78","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/78"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level III","synonyms":null,"description":"Apply, analyze, evaluate, and create (implementing, organizing, and critiquing information)","p